# Lambda Orientation

<span class="lead"> </span>

Lambda Launch material is now updated and available in Canvas. As of August, all material shown in Training Kit is deprecated.

## [Learning at Lambda](../module/recBC1BCvLsTSiaLS)

Welcome to Lambda School! We are so excited to have you as a student and begin this amazing journey with you as you launch your new career. Lambda Launch material is now updated and available in Canvas. As of August, all material shown in Training Kit is deprecated.

#### Objectives:

- Student should be able to know how to navigate and communicate using Slack.
- Student should be able to know how to access and participate fully and professionally in Zoom.
- Student should be able to know how to access and navigate Training Kit
- Student should be able to know how to access and navigate the Progress Report Dashboard.
- Student should be able to know how to access and ask a question in Frontdesk.
- Student should be able to know how to access and navigate Google Calendar.
- Student should be able to identify the requirements of the ISA.
- Student should be able to understand the I do, we do, you do structure of Lambda school curriculum and how it is valuable for learning.
- Student should be able to understand the difference between traditional grading and outcomes based assessments.
- Student should be able to articulate the academic expectations, attendance expectation and daily work routine of Lambda School classes.

## [Labs and Beyond](../module/recnBWTWXqXWjWCUd)

Lambda Launch material is now updated and available in Canvas. As of August, all material shown in Training Kit is deprecated. School’s goal is to find untapped or underutilized talent, and train that talent for the most in-demand jobs in the world. This module will cover our careers curriculum, labs, Lambda X and the endorsement process.

#### Objectives:

- Student should be able to develop a framework of success through explaining careers lessons, Lambda X and endorsements.
- Student should be able to understand the basics of the career and professional development curriculum
- Student should be able to articulate how Lambda supports them in their job search and the importance of becoming endorsed
- Student should be able to understand that the Lambda curriculum has a singular focus on career readiness.
- Student should be able to know how to access and participate in school engagement opportunities.

## [Values and Support](../module/rec7Vyq18G1tytzyk)

Lambda Launch material is now updated and available in Canvas. As of August, all material shown in Training Kit is deprecated. School is much more than a school. It’s a community. It’s a job placement agency. We’re a group of highly-motivated individuals striving to make entry into the tech industry more accessible by providing educational opportunities to underrepresented and underserved individuals.

#### Objectives:

- Student should be able to identify school mission, vision and values.
- Student should be able to integrate with the school culture and understand the code of conduct expectations.
- Student should be able to clearly articulate why they have chosen to attend Lambda School.
- Student should be able to know who to ask for help and how to ask for help at Lambda School
- Student should be able to identify what a growth mindset means and how it applies to everyday life at Lambda School.
- Student should be able to identify the school services available to support their educational and personal goals and how to access them.
- Student should be able to develop a spirit of independent learning through self-direction, self-reflection, and advocacy.
- Student should be able to see themselves as a professional employee and understand the necessity to develop the social and academic skills needed for a professional employee.
